<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Docker/Kubernetes provides a nice way to output data using custom go templates. </p> <p>Inspired by them this library also provides custom outputs to your own command line tools.</p> <p>Setting up <strong>teks</strong> and making your output fits into go templated output can be done in a glimpse. </p> <p>Repo: <a href="https://github.com/kasvith/teks">https://github.com/kasvith/teks</a></p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p><a href="https://i.redd.it/ipafsnh1xb231.png">teks</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/kasvith"> /u/kasvith </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/golang/comments/bwnn6s/teks_awesome_templated_output_for_your_cli_tool/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/golang/comments/bwnn6s/teks_awesome_templated_output_for_your_cli_tool/">[comments]</a></span>